Several cabinet ministers including Police Minister Bheki Cele, former State Security Minister Ayanda Dlodlo, Justice Minister Ronald Lamola and Trade and Industry Minister Ebrahim Patel also gave evidence during the hearings earlier this year. Over 300 people died and businesses were destroyed during days of looting and violence that swept through Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal provinces last year. Ramaphosa will testify with regard to his responsibility as the Head of State. SAHRC Commissioner Andre Gaum said the Hearing Panel will reconvene on Friday April 1, 2022 when the President of the Republic of South Africa will appear and give evidence in regard to the July 2021 unrest. --SABC--